00:31:17.360 --> 00:31:18.490
And I think for [INAUDIBLE]

00:31:18.490 --> 00:31:19.917
I feel like Ray Kurzweil.

00:31:19.917 --> 00:31:21.050
AUDIENCE: What's that?

00:31:21.050 --> 00:31:21.090
JON RONSON: Nothing.

00:31:21.090 --> 00:31:21.910
It's OK.

00:31:21.910 --> 00:31:23.590
[LAUGHTER]

00:31:23.590 --> 00:31:24.850
AUDIENCE: So, question.

00:31:24.850 --> 00:31:28.650
How young do children
start to exhibit

00:31:28.650 --> 00:31:29.620
some of these qualities?

00:31:29.620 --> 00:31:33.850
And are there tests that are
specifically geared for them?

00:31:33.850 --> 00:31:36.130
JON RONSON: There's actually
camps. "The New York Times"

00:31:36.130 --> 00:31:38.930
did this incredible piece, a few
months ago, about summer

00:31:38.930 --> 00:31:42.820
camps for psychopathic
children.

00:31:42.820 --> 00:31:47.920
Because the fact is, one of the
items on the checklist is

00:31:47.920 --> 00:31:49.730
early behavior problems.

00:31:49.730 --> 00:31:51.690
And the behavior tends
to manifest

00:31:51.690 --> 00:31:53.530
itself from the ages--

00:31:53.530 --> 00:31:54.560
almost always, actually.

00:31:54.560 --> 00:31:56.540
This surprised me, when I asked
Robert Hare about this.

00:31:56.540 --> 00:31:58.530
He said this was
like a big one.

00:31:58.530 --> 00:32:01.830
Between the ages of 8 and 10.

00:32:01.830 --> 00:32:05.170
And that's obviously an age when
you're thinking about PR,

00:32:05.170 --> 00:32:07.370
and you're not thinking about
your career, so you will

00:32:07.370 --> 00:32:12.880
display these characteristics
in a pretty open way.

00:32:12.880 --> 00:32:15.520
And it's either 8 and
10 or 10 and 12.

00:32:15.520 --> 00:32:16.952
I think it might be 10
and 12, actually.

00:32:16.952 --> 00:32:19.262
I think I've got that wrong.

00:32:19.262 --> 00:32:22.650
Al Dunlap's saying that he had
no early behavior problems,

00:32:22.650 --> 00:32:26.000
and if he'd got accepted into
West Point, that proves it,

00:32:26.000 --> 00:32:29.610
shows that he's actually not, as
much as we all want him to

00:32:29.610 --> 00:32:33.250
be, a classic psychopath.

00:32:33.250 --> 00:32:35.720
So yes, between the ages of--

00:32:35.720 --> 00:32:37.040
it's either 8 and
10 or 10 and 12.

00:32:37.040 --> 00:32:38.630
I can't remember.

00:32:38.630 --> 00:32:41.260
And there's an incredible "New
York Times" piece, which if

00:32:41.260 --> 00:32:44.080
anybody wants to read more
about the possibility of

00:32:44.080 --> 00:32:48.002
psychopathic children, I would
recommend you read that.

00:32:48.002 --> 00:32:50.810
Thanks.

00:32:50.810 --> 00:32:51.460
Hey.

00:32:51.460 --> 00:32:52.140
AUDIENCE: Hey.

00:32:52.140 --> 00:32:54.550
So your stories are just
